Making use of rapid prototyping capabilities, the reactor was adapted such that a second window was installed in the bottom opposite to the first window to enable transmission measurements. Furthermore, the reactor was additionally manufactured with channel heights of z = 10mm and z = 5mm. The results are depicted in Table 3. No linear correlation was found when considering all measured optical depths, indicating that at least the 20mm measurement is within analytical limits. Consequently, only optical depths of z = 10mm and z = 5mm were used to determine the extinction coefficient to β ≈ 232m− 1. With this extinction coefficient it can be estimated that around 0.5% of the light is transmitted after an optical depth of 10mm.
